# Flowchart v2 Architecture

## Structure
- Pure RN Views in flex column for step boxes (no fixed Y constants)
- SVG overlay using onLayout measurements for arrows, diamonds, callout boxes
- `ready` flag gates SVG rendering until all measurements collected

## Canvas constants
- W = 470, BW = 440, GAP = 24, STEP_PADDING_V = 10
- Diamond column: DW = 240, DCX = 135, DXR = 255
- Callout: CBW = 140, CBX = 315
- Wide callout variant: CBW_D1 = 170, CBX_D1 = 285

## Arrow routing rules
- All vertical arrows from a diamond use DCX (135), NOT cx (235).
  Diagonal arrows = wrong x-coordinate. Common bug.
- No arrow between EMT bar and first step
- Arrow terminates at PARAMEDIC bar TOP, no arrow exits bar bottom
- No GAP spacers after section bars
- No arrow exits a SectionHeader into the next step box. Section headers function as visual dividers — adding an arrow after them creates redundant noise. Same principle as the existing rule that no arrow exits the bottom of a section bar (EMT/PARAMEDIC bars). This applies to ALL flowcharts going forward.
- No arrows connect the title block, caution callouts, excludes callouts, or any header/contextual blocks above the first EMT step. These are descriptive context, not sequential flow. The first arrow in any flowchart appears between Step 1 and Step 2 (or Step 1 and the next sequential step). This applies to ALL flowcharts going forward.

## Arrow labels
- Downward YES/NO labels: manual SvgText elements, offset 14px right of arrow shaft
  at midpoint+4. NEVER use Arrow component's label prop for these (overlaps diamond tips).
- Horizontal YES labels (diamond → callout): SvgText centered above line at midpoint - 6

## Step box visual rules
- Step label uses subColor (muted); step title uses bodyColor
- ScopeBadge uses `tone` prop so badge colors match box theme
  (no green PARAMEDIC badges on orange/red boxes)
- Drug-administration boxes: orange (critBg / critBorder)
- Defibrillate box: RED, not orange. Do not change this.
- Critical transport destination callouts: red (destBg / destBorder / destText)
- Callout box heights computed dynamically from text metrics, NEVER hardcoded

## Font Size Standards
- Source of truth: `components/protocols/SeizureFlowchart.tsx`
- Step title: 17px / 700 weight
- Step body text and bullets: 14px / 20px lineHeight
- Drug subtitle (dose lines): 14px / 20px lineHeight / 600 weight
- Step label ("Step N", "Option A"): 12px / 800 weight / letterSpacing 1
- Section header text: 14px / 700 weight / letterSpacing 1.2
- Caution/Excludes title labels: 13px / 800 weight
- Caution/Excludes body text: 15px
- Caution secondary/explanatory text: 13px
- ScopeBadge text: 11px / 800 weight
- SVG callout title text: 12px / 700 weight
- SVG callout body text: 11px
- These are minimum standards for legibility on phone viewports (Note 10+ tested at 6.8 inches). Do not go smaller. Larger may be appropriate for less dense protocols.

## Color tokens
EMT:           bg #21262d   border #484f58   title #e6edf3   sub #8b949e
Paramedic:     bg #1b3a2d   border #0F6E56   title #56d364   sub #8fcca0
Critical/Drug: bg #2a1a0a   border #f0883e   title #f0883e   sub #d29922
Decision:      bg #1f3a5f   border #185FA5   text  #79c0ff
Destination:   bg #3a1010   border #d62828   text  #f85149   sub  #e89b9b
Pediatric:     bg #0a1a2a   border #1f6feb   drug  #58a6ff   dose #a5d6ff
Warning/Amber: bg #1a1400   border #9e6a03   text  #d29922
Purple:        bg #1c1029   border #8957e5   title #d2a8ff   sub  #b083f0

## Purple usage
Purple is the "differentiating clinical move" token. Used on Cardiac Arrest
Non-Shockable's H's & T's grid. Use sparingly — if every protocol has purple,
the signal becomes noise.